page.title: 05YEOVIL MARSH VILLAGE
page.content: The corner house used to be a basket makers called{'Chedzoys'}.There were no Council houses,only a field owned by Mr.Lock.There was a Wheelwright, they worked at{'Carents Cottage'}. Today,the Bungalow and the Cottage in the village are the buildings of a family row of cottages.Chapel court is the chapel converted into a dwelling. {The Elms,Little Cranford,Northolme {House}were not there but the site was a field with Nissan huts and search lights which were used in the war. Woodrow cottages used to belong to{ {'Carents Farm'}but now belong to Woodrow Farm.The{Coign}and{Little {Cranford}were built between 1967 and 1969 and are exactly the same.
